In [2]:
 # ---------------------------- MODEL DEFINITION ----------------------------

# Define the CNN model
face_mask_model = Sequential([
    # First convolutional layer with 100 filters, kernel size 3x3, ReLU activation, input shape 150x150x3
    Conv2D(100, (3,3), activation='relu', input_shape=(150, 150, 3)),
    MaxPooling2D(2, 2),  # Max-pooling with 2x2 pool size to reduce dimensions

    # Second convolutional layer with 100 filters, kernel size 3x3, ReLU activation
    Conv2D(100, (3,3), activation='relu'),
    MaxPooling2D(2, 2),  # Max-pooling with 2x2 pool size

    Flatten(),          # Flatten the feature maps to a 1D feature vector
    Dropout(0.5),       # Dropout layer to prevent overfitting (drops 50% of neurons randomly)
    
    Dense(50, activation='relu'),  # Fully connected layer with 50 neurons and ReLU activation
    Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')  # Output layer with 1 neuron and sigmoid activation (binary classification)
])

# Compile the model with optimizer, loss, and metrics
face_mask_model.compile(optimizer='adam',                  # Adam optimizer for adaptive learning
                        loss='binary_crossentropy',        # Binary cross-entropy for 2-class classification
                        metrics=['acc'])                   # Metric to track accuracy

# ---------------------------- DATA PREPROCESSING ----------------------------

# Define path to training data directory
TRAINING_PATH = "./train"

# Data augmentation and rescaling for training images
train_data_gen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rescale=1.0/255,                # Normalize pixel values to [0, 1]
    rotation_range=40,              # Rotate images by up to 40 degrees
    width_shift_range=0.2,          # Randomly shift width by 20%
    height_shift_range=0.2,         # Randomly shift height by 20%
    shear_range=0.2,                # Apply shearing transformation
    zoom_range=0.2,                 # Apply random zoom
    horizontal_flip=True,           # Flip images horizontally
    fill_mode='nearest'             # Fill missing pixels with nearest value
)

# Create training data generator from directory
train_generator = train_data_gen.flow_from_directory(
    TRAINING_PATH,                   # Path to training dataset
    batch_size=32,                   # Number of images per batch
    target_size=(150, 150),          # Resize images to 150x150 pixels
    class_mode='binary',              # Binary classification mode
    shuffle=True                      # Ensure data is shuffled
)

# Define path to validation data directory
VALIDATION_PATH = "./test"

# Data rescaling for validation images
validation_data_gen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1.0/255)

# Create validation data generator from directory
validation_generator = validation_data_gen.flow_from_directory(
    VALIDATION_PATH,                 # Path to validation dataset
    batch_size=32,                   # Number of images per batch
    target_size=(150, 150),          # Resize images to 150x150 pixels
    class_mode='binary',             # Binary classification mode
    shuffle=True                     # Ensure data is shuffled
)

# Stop training when validation loss does not improve for 3 consecutive epochs
early_stopping = EarlyStopping(
    monitor='val_loss',              # Monitor validation loss
    patience=3,                      # Number of epochs to wait before stopping
    verbose=1,                       # Display information when stopping
    restore_best_weights=True        # Restore the best weights after stopping
)

from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix
import seaborn as sns

# Load the best saved model
model = load_model('face_mask_detect_model.keras')

# Prepare test/validation data for evaluation
test_generator = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255).flow_from_directory(
    VALIDATION_PATH,
    target_size=(150, 150),
    batch_size=1,          # Use batch size 1 for precise prediction mapping
    class_mode='binary',
    shuffle=False          # Disable shuffling to align predictions and labels
)

# Predict on the validation/test data
pred_probs = model.predict(test_generator, verbose=1)
pred_labels = (pred_probs > 0.5).astype(int).flatten()  # Convert to 0 or 1

# True labels
true_labels = test_generator.classes

# Get class label names
class_names = list(test_generator.class_indices.keys())

# Classification Report
print("\nClassification Report:\n")
print(classification_report(true_labels, pred_labels, target_names=class_names))

# Confusion Matrix
conf_mat = confusion_matrix(true_labels, pred_labels)

# Plot confusion matrix using seaborn
plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))
sns.heatmap(conf_mat, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues',
            xticklabels=class_names, yticklabels=class_names)
plt.xlabel('Predicted')
plt.ylabel('Actual')
plt.title('Confusion Matrix')
plt.show()

# Evaluate accuracy
test_loss, test_acc = model.evaluate(test_generator)
print(f"Test Accuracy: {test_acc:.4f}")

from flask import Flask, render_template, request
from keras.models import load_model
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing import image
import numpy as np
import os

app = Flask(__name__,template_folder='template')
model = load_model('face_mask_detect_model.keras')

UPLOAD_FOLDER = './static/uploads'
app.config['UPLOAD_FOLDER'] = UPLOAD_FOLDER

# Label Mapping
class_names = ['Mask', 'No Mask']

@app.route('/')
def home():
    return render_template('index.html')

@app.route('/predict', methods=['POST'])
def predict():
    if 'file' not in request.files:
        return 'No file part'

    file = request.files['file']
    if file.filename == '':
        return 'No selected file'

    filepath = os.path.join(app.config['UPLOAD_FOLDER'], file.filename)
    file.save(filepath)

    # Preprocess the image
    img = image.load_img(filepath, target_size=(150, 150))
    img_array = image.img_to_array(img) / 255.0
    img_array = np.expand_dims(img_array, axis=0)

    # Predict
    prediction = model.predict(img_array)[0][0]
    label = class_names[0] if prediction < 0.5 else class_names[1]
    confidence = 1 - prediction if prediction < 0.5 else prediction

    return render_template('index.html', 
                           prediction=label, 
                           confidence=f"{confidence:.2f}",
                           image_path=filepath)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(debug=False)
